    "Exchanging the IDs with numerals (1-10) for each abstract during fine-tuning could potentially solve this issue.",
    "This is something we plan to try in the next iteration of the dataset and training.",
    "In terms of recall values for relevant abstracts, based on the manual evaluation of 10 examples from PQAref test set both fine-tuned models performed better, exhibiting a 47% and 5% improvement over their versions in zero-shot mode.",
    "The situation is slightly different for the same 10 questions with abstracts retrieved using our IR.",
    "While recall values of M1 were still superior, especially compared to 0-M1 with 27% improvement, 0-M2 performed slightly better than M2 (1% difference)."
